WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
-= www.OpenSubtitles.org =-

00:40.040 --> 00:42.959
l have a friend, Deborah,
a psychologist...

00:43.127 --> 00:45.294
...who was asked
by the city of Philadelphia...

00:45.462 --> 00:49.549
...if she could offer psychological
counseling to Cambodian refugees...

00:49.717 --> 00:53.261
...boat people,
who had recently arrived in the city.

00:53.429 --> 00:56.556
Deborah was daunted by the task.
These Cambodians...

00:56.724 --> 01:01.728
...had suffered genocide, starvation,
relatives murdered before their eyes...

01:01.895 --> 01:05.648
...years in refugee camps,
harrowing boat trips to the West.

01:06.108 --> 01:07.984
How could she relate
to their suffering?

01:08.152 --> 01:09.819
How could she help these people?

01:16.201 --> 01:18.703
So guess what all these people
wanted to talk about...

01:18.871 --> 01:21.622
...with my friend Deborah,
the psychologist.

01:23.709 --> 01:26.544
lt was all,
"l met this guy in the refugee camp.

01:26.712 --> 01:29.547
I thought he really loved me,
but when we got separated...

01:29.715 --> 01:32.300
...he took up with my cousin.
Now he says he loves me...

01:32.468 --> 01:35.928
...and keeps calling me. They're
married now. What should l do?"

01:36.096 --> 01:37.180
This is how we are.

01:37.347 --> 01:38.556
May I help you?

01:38.724 --> 01:41.392
I'm Liz Gilbert. I'm writing
a magazine article on Bali.

01:41.560 --> 01:43.019
I wanted to meet a medicine man.

01:43.187 --> 01:46.272
Everyone said I should meet
Ketut Liyer. Am l in the right place?

01:46.440 --> 01:47.523
Wait.

01:47.691 --> 01:52.028
l mean, here I am with
a ninth-generation medicine man...

01:52.196 --> 01:54.697
...and what do I wanna
ask him about?

01:54.865 --> 01:57.200
Getting closer to God?

01:57.367 --> 02:00.912
Saving the world's
starving children?

02:01.663 --> 02:04.207
Happy to see you. l am Ketut Liyer.

02:04.374 --> 02:09.294
Nope. l wanna discuss
my relationship.

02:12.591 --> 02:15.134
You are a world traveler.

02:15.302 --> 02:17.386
You will live a long time...

02:17.554 --> 02:20.890
...have many friends,
many experiences.

02:22.476 --> 02:26.145
You will have two marriages.
One long, one short.

02:26.480 --> 02:28.272
Am l in the long one
or the short one?

02:28.816 --> 02:30.358
Can't tell.

02:30.526 --> 02:34.487
Also you will lose all your money.

02:35.572 --> 02:38.825
I think in next six to 1 0 months.

02:40.118 --> 02:43.204
Don't worry.
You will get it all back again.

02:43.914 --> 02:46.290
And you will come back to Bali...

02:46.458 --> 02:52.755
...and live here for three or four
months and teach me English.

02:52.923 --> 02:56.384
I never had anybody
to practice my English with.

02:57.135 --> 02:58.719
And then...

02:58.887 --> 03:04.267
...l will teach you everything l know.

03:07.104 --> 03:08.938
Wait.

03:13.151 --> 03:15.069
I have this for you.

03:15.237 --> 03:18.698
Keep grounded so it's like
you have four legs.

03:19.116 --> 03:21.367
That way, you can stay in this world.

03:21.952 --> 03:25.913
Also, no looking at world
through your head.

03:26.081 --> 03:28.499
Look through your heart instead.

03:28.667 --> 03:30.793
That way, you will know God.

03:32.254 --> 03:34.463
Which is why you came here, no?

03:35.632 --> 03:39.051
See you later, alligator.

03:53.442 --> 03:56.819
I proofread all of her manuscripts.

03:56.987 --> 04:00.489
My wife is very, very beautiful,
but she can't spell for anything.

04:00.657 --> 04:03.326
Look at Uncle Stephen.

04:04.828 --> 04:05.995
And Auntie Liz.

04:06.163 --> 04:09.874
I'm counting the minutes for this to be
over so l can get in my big girl pants.

04:10.042 --> 04:12.001
You look fantastic.
You just had a baby.

04:12.169 --> 04:14.170
Oh, you're lying.
I'm fat, I'm exhausted...

04:14.338 --> 04:16.880
...l can't keep two thoughts.
I feel like Liza Minnelli.

04:17.048 --> 04:18.716
Stephen, can you hold Jack?

04:18.884 --> 04:21.218
-l'm gonna introduce you to Walter.
-Yeah.

04:22.012 --> 04:25.431
Hey, dude, you wanna grab a beer
or something?

04:25.682 --> 04:28.309
My new book comes out in April.
Thank you for asking.

04:28.477 --> 04:29.518
-Great.
-May.

04:29.686 --> 04:31.020
May. May.

04:31.688 --> 04:34.482
This is Andre. You two are
Times' Most Notable nominees.

04:34.650 --> 04:37.360
-So glad to finally meet you.
-Nice to finally meet you.

04:39.363 --> 04:41.072
I fed him nachos. ls that bad?

04:41.239 --> 04:43.741
You look comfortable.
What'd you feed him, chloroform?

04:43.909 --> 04:45.868
-Give him to his dad.
-l told you, nachos.

04:46.036 --> 04:48.579
Know what? I'd be asleep too
if l had a dump like that.

04:48.747 --> 04:51.749
-We'll give him to his mom.
-Come here then.

04:53.377 --> 04:55.503
-Wanna help me change his diaper?
-Yes, I do.

04:55.671 --> 04:57.546
Hey, how's the vintage car
thing going?

04:57.714 --> 05:00.508
Oh, no, no, no. l changed jobs.
I'm a pastry chef now.

05:00.676 --> 05:02.802
-You mean you're a baker.
-Yeah.

05:02.970 --> 05:04.720
You wanna get baked?

05:06.223 --> 05:08.849
I know, I know.

05:09.017 --> 05:11.060
It's hard, isn't it?

05:11.561 --> 05:15.356
Oh, no. This is so much fun.

05:15.899 --> 05:18.526
Did you know the exact moment
you wanted to have a baby?

05:18.694 --> 05:23.197
I can't remember, but l've had the box
since before l got married.

05:23.365 --> 05:24.907
What box?

05:25.075 --> 05:28.202
It's girly and embarrassing,
and you'll laugh at me if I tell you.

05:28.662 --> 05:31.664
I will laugh at you,
but you still have to tell me.

05:32.249 --> 05:34.000
Come on.

05:34.668 --> 05:36.168
Under the bed.

05:42.551 --> 05:45.261
I've been filling it with baby things...

05:45.429 --> 05:48.264
...waiting until Andy
was ready to be a father.

05:50.350 --> 05:53.227
So sweet.

05:53.395 --> 05:55.062
Does this come in my size?

06:01.111 --> 06:04.613
I have a box just like this, except
it's filled with National Geographics...

06:04.781 --> 06:06.949
...and The Times travel section.

06:07.117 --> 06:10.244
All the places l wanna see
before l die.

06:10.412 --> 06:14.874
Liz, having a baby is like
getting a tattoo on your face.

06:16.293 --> 06:18.461
You kind of wanna be
fully committed.

06:22.424 --> 06:25.801
So my trip to Aruba next week,
which is just a basic, you know...

06:25.969 --> 06:28.596
..."where to sleep, swim
and stuff your face" piece....

06:28.764 --> 06:30.222
I got a new bikini.

06:30.390 --> 06:33.893
And it turns out,
I have unlimited minibar access.

06:34.061 --> 06:35.895
-You know what that means?
-Jet lag?

06:36.063 --> 06:38.773
You, me...

06:38.940 --> 06:40.316
...macadamia nuts.

06:41.860 --> 06:42.943
That was cute.

06:43.111 --> 06:46.322
You know who l was talking to
at the party who was really inspiring...

06:46.490 --> 06:47.865
-...was Tara's friend.
-Brian.

06:48.033 --> 06:51.202
Brian. Unbelievable.
He's a teacher, you know that?

06:51.369 --> 06:53.120
He's a substitute teacher, isn't he?

06:53.288 --> 06:56.332
Yeah. He was talking about the
budget cuts that are happening now.

06:56.500 --> 06:58.250
There's no money for anything.

06:58.418 --> 07:01.087
There's no music classes,
there's no arts classes.

07:01.254 --> 07:04.215
They're volunteering their time
to do all of this after school.

07:04.382 --> 07:06.425
They're educating our kids,
you know?

07:06.593 --> 07:09.470
I think you'd make
a great teacher, honey.

07:09.638 --> 07:12.848
Thank you,
but I was thinking more of like...

07:13.433 --> 07:16.769
...education. Getting my masters,
going back to school. l don't know.

07:16.937 --> 07:18.604
You know?

07:25.362 --> 07:27.488
I-- You know....

07:28.115 --> 07:30.699
-Going back to school.
-l'm just thinking out loud.

07:33.245 --> 07:38.290
I was getting the sinking feeling that
Ketut's prophecy was coming true.

07:38.458 --> 07:41.127
Was l in the shorter marriage?

07:42.879 --> 07:45.881
We'd only bought this house
a year ago.

07:46.550 --> 07:47.967
Hadn't I wanted this?

07:50.428 --> 07:54.723
I had actively participated
in every moment of the creation...

07:54.891 --> 07:56.725
...of this life.

07:56.893 --> 08:00.229
So why didn't I see myself
in any of it?

08:05.652 --> 08:09.572
The only thing more impossible
than staying...

08:09.739 --> 08:11.615
...was leaving.

08:13.243 --> 08:17.413
I didn't wanna hurt anybody. l wanted
to slip quietly out the back door...

08:17.581 --> 08:21.083
...and not stop running
until l reached Greenland.

08:25.547 --> 08:28.090
lnstead, l made a decision.

08:28.717 --> 08:30.426
To pray.

08:30.677 --> 08:34.096
You know, like, to God.

08:34.806 --> 08:39.351
And it was such a foreign concept to
me, that l swear l almost began with:

08:39.519 --> 08:41.520
"l'm a big fan of your work."

08:48.737 --> 08:50.821
Hello, God?

08:53.700 --> 08:56.785
Nice to finally meet you. l....

08:57.704 --> 09:03.959
I am sorry l've never spoken
directly to you before...

09:04.127 --> 09:05.794
...but...

09:06.630 --> 09:09.465
...l hope l've expressed my...

09:10.133 --> 09:14.178
...ample gratitude for all
the blessings you've given...

09:14.346 --> 09:16.639
...to me in my life.

09:26.483 --> 09:28.984
I'm in serious trouble.

09:30.987 --> 09:33.322
I don't know what to do.

09:34.658 --> 09:37.159
I need an answer.

09:37.661 --> 09:41.872
Please, tell me what to do.

09:43.416 --> 09:46.335
Oh, God, help me, please.

09:52.509 --> 09:55.469
Tell me what to do and l'll do it.

09:58.306 --> 10:01.016
Go back to bed, Liz.

10:22.414 --> 10:24.373
I don't wanna go to Aruba.

10:28.003 --> 10:30.629
I don't wanna be married.

10:47.939 --> 10:50.733
You know, there's a whole
divorce section downstairs.

11:09.502 --> 11:11.086
-"Pepper grinder."
-She's having...

11:11.254 --> 11:13.464
-...a nervous breakdown.
-This is what girls do.

11:13.631 --> 11:16.133
-She's processing.
-Why doesn't she get drunk or laid?

11:16.301 --> 11:18.302
That's what l would do if you left me.

11:18.470 --> 11:19.845
No, you wouldn't.

11:20.013 --> 11:22.723
-No, I wouldn't.
-She moved out, she filed for divorce.

11:22.891 --> 11:26.185
They were together eight years.
She's got no home.

11:33.276 --> 11:35.194
"Legacy."

11:37.781 --> 11:42.618
Every word in Italian is like a truffle.
A magic trick.

11:43.119 --> 11:46.163
Honey, l get it.
It's your life raft right now.

11:46.331 --> 11:49.583
When Andy and l broke up
for two weeks, l bought a loom.

11:49.751 --> 11:52.586
A frigging loom.
And he tried to start a microbrewery.

11:52.754 --> 11:55.714
I don't know how you guys
aren't sick of me now. I'm sick of me.

11:55.882 --> 11:58.133
Are you kidding me?
We love having you.

11:58.301 --> 12:00.427
It's kind of like having
a writer in residence.

12:00.595 --> 12:03.097
But you are a writer.
You should be writing something.

12:03.264 --> 12:07.434
Maybe I could write about a woman
who goes to Italy to learn ltalian.

12:07.602 --> 12:11.063
Call it
Carbohydrates and Conjugations.

12:11.231 --> 12:13.774
I'll start looking for a place.

12:15.527 --> 12:18.237
-l'm falling in love with you.
-l'm not who you think I am.

12:18.405 --> 12:19.905
I'm just your fantasy.

12:20.073 --> 12:24.284
No, that's bullshit. You're real.

12:25.161 --> 12:27.454
Your scars, your talent.

12:27.622 --> 12:29.706
The fact that
I own a piece-of-crap bar...

12:29.874 --> 12:32.126
...and you accept that
that's all l'm gonna do.

12:32.293 --> 12:33.669
Okay, this sucks.

12:33.837 --> 12:36.338
-l second that.
-Don't be rude.

12:43.430 --> 12:45.556
I love your pain.

12:46.307 --> 12:50.269
And l love that when we're together,
I can make it go away.

12:51.354 --> 12:52.855
-Oh, he's good.
-You're love...

12:53.022 --> 12:56.692
-He's hot, there's a difference.
-...is like a hot panini.

12:56.860 --> 13:01.989
And when I look into your eyes,
I hear dolphins clapping.

13:02.157 --> 13:04.658
I did not write that line.

13:04.826 --> 13:06.326
Here's what he doesn't know yet.

13:07.579 --> 13:11.290
I disappear into the person l love.

13:11.458 --> 13:16.378
I am the permeable membrane.
If l love you, you can have it all.

13:16.546 --> 13:19.381
My money, my time, my body...

13:19.549 --> 13:23.051
...my dog, my dog's money.

13:23.219 --> 13:26.388
I will assume your debts
and project upon you...

13:26.556 --> 13:31.727
...all sorts of nifty qualities you've
never actually cultivated in yourself.

13:31.895 --> 13:34.480
I will give you all this and more...

13:34.647 --> 13:37.483
...until l am so exhausted
and depleted...

13:37.650 --> 13:40.486
...the only way l can recover...

13:40.653 --> 13:43.197
...is by becoming infatuated
with someone else.

13:50.413 --> 13:52.623
-Elizabeth, hi.
-Hi.

13:52.790 --> 13:54.416
Oh, really?

13:57.337 --> 13:59.421
How you doing?

14:30.703 --> 14:32.454
Cheers.

14:34.123 --> 14:36.583
-Thank you.
-l owe you an apology.

14:36.751 --> 14:40.629
-For the walkouts.
-Well, l'm not everyone's cup of tea.

14:41.381 --> 14:43.340
I doubt that.

14:44.092 --> 14:46.093
I, on the other hand, was shit.

14:46.886 --> 14:51.640
-Although l was trying very hard.
-"Shit" is a strong word.

14:52.308 --> 14:53.517
Thank you.

14:53.685 --> 14:56.645
You seem shorter in person
than on the stage.

14:56.813 --> 14:58.730
-Really? l hear that a lot.
-Sorry.

14:58.898 --> 15:00.440
It's okay.

15:01.234 --> 15:03.360
It's unnerving when...

15:03.528 --> 15:07.489
...a total stranger sees you
more clearly than you see yourself.

15:07.657 --> 15:09.908
That's what l mean
by saying you're short.

15:14.330 --> 15:17.583
Are you hearing dolphins clapping
right now?

15:18.918 --> 15:22.337
I took a few liberties
with your material.

15:22.505 --> 15:25.799
I give you full permission to make
fun of me. I know you're dying to.

15:27.510 --> 15:30.387
You're far too charming
to make fun of.

15:34.767 --> 15:37.019
I'm still hearing them.

15:45.987 --> 15:48.322
Is that your guru?

15:49.407 --> 15:52.284
You're joking, but, yes, it is.

15:53.578 --> 15:55.495
She's beautiful.

15:55.663 --> 15:58.332
Yeah. A friend told me about her.

15:59.208 --> 16:02.127
I was out of work and feeling
pretty desperate for something.

16:02.295 --> 16:05.130
Not the last time I was out of work,
the time before that.

16:05.298 --> 16:10.552
And l just had this feeling like
I was looking in all the wrong places.

16:10.720 --> 16:11.970
Looking for what?

16:12.305 --> 16:13.347
God.

16:14.932 --> 16:18.268
She has an ashram in India.
I'm dying to go, but...

16:18.436 --> 16:21.772
...you know, you have to get, like,
three stages of hepatitis shots...

16:21.939 --> 16:24.816
...and my insurance always runs out.

16:25.026 --> 16:26.943
I'll go when the time's right.

16:27.111 --> 16:30.280
There's a gathering of her students
every morning.

16:31.407 --> 16:34.409
If you want,
I could take you sometime.

16:34.577 --> 16:39.915
If you're not unnerved by 1 00
crunchy people chanting in Sanskrit.

16:40.750 --> 16:43.001
I need to be unnerved.

17:13.907 --> 17:17.577
David. A yogi from Yonkers.

17:19.122 --> 17:22.499
I didn't exactly fall in love
with the guy.

17:23.917 --> 17:26.586
What happened was
I dove out of my marriage...

17:26.753 --> 17:28.380
...and into David's arms...

17:28.548 --> 17:31.800
...exactly the same way
a cartoon circus performer...

17:31.968 --> 17:36.596
...dives off a high platform
and into a small cup of water...

17:37.014 --> 17:38.473
...vanishing completely.

17:47.400 --> 17:50.068
Your underwear, my queen.

17:53.656 --> 17:56.241
He just folded my delicates.

17:56.409 --> 18:00.120
Oh, my God, baby,
you are in so much trouble.

18:52.173 --> 18:53.548
Thirty-six?

19:07.230 --> 19:09.731
My client is simply not interested
in a divorce.

19:11.609 --> 19:13.777
Is he serious?

19:13.945 --> 19:15.821
Is he really representing himself?

19:15.988 --> 19:18.073
One semester of law school
right here, baby.

19:18.241 --> 19:20.992
Great. Well, what would it take
to interest your client?

19:21.577 --> 19:24.746
Okay, so here's the deal.
You have screwed up my life...

19:24.914 --> 19:27.791
...but what l wanna know
is why couldn't you find yourself...

19:27.959 --> 19:30.836
...in our marriage? Why didn't you
say what you were thinking?

19:31.003 --> 19:33.505
-l did. You never listened to me.
-No. You never said:

19:33.673 --> 19:36.424
"Hey, you know what?
You suck. l'm deeply unhappy."

19:36.592 --> 19:39.928
You just took off. You never gave me
a chance to address those problems.

19:40.096 --> 19:42.931
That's not fair. That's just quitting.
I took vows.

19:43.099 --> 19:46.017
Till death.
And l take them seriously.

19:46.519 --> 19:49.396
I believe this is just a phase
and l'm willing to wait it out.

19:49.564 --> 19:51.022
You are always waiting, Stephen.

19:51.190 --> 19:53.441
Waiting for me to come home,
to wanna have kids...

19:53.609 --> 19:56.278
...to make you dinner.
I don't know why we can't accept...

19:56.445 --> 19:58.613
...we don't wanna live
in unhappiness anymore.

19:58.781 --> 20:01.283
I accept the fact that
I am occasionally unreliable...

20:01.450 --> 20:04.703
...and l often get sidetracked,
but I thought you liked that about me.

20:04.871 --> 20:07.205
I thought it was okay
that I had hopes and dreams.

20:07.373 --> 20:10.959
Have a dream. Stephen, great,
fine. Do that. Just pick one.

20:11.127 --> 20:13.128
Okay, l pick one. I pick you.

20:22.930 --> 20:25.348
I know this is awful.

20:26.726 --> 20:31.396
But l believe with every molecule of
my body that you will find the person...

20:31.564 --> 20:34.149
...that wants just what you want.

20:34.317 --> 20:37.652
That will give you what you want
and what you deserve. l'm not her.

20:38.070 --> 20:42.157
Well, you obviously know nothing
about what l want.

20:45.244 --> 20:47.495
My client would like to submit
a song he wrote...

20:47.663 --> 20:52.000
...that he believes is relevant to these
proceedings. Goes something like this:

20:53.002 --> 20:54.628
Are you kidding?

20:58.841 --> 21:01.134
Quitter, quitter, quitter!

21:01.302 --> 21:04.262
How about l take the blame?
I am the one who couldn't deal...

21:04.430 --> 21:07.432
...with another weekend roaming
some box-shaped superstore...

21:07.600 --> 21:09.142
...buying appliances on credit...

21:09.310 --> 21:13.480
...and pretending to be a couple that
neither one of us ever knew how to be.

21:13.648 --> 21:15.023
You wanted that toaster.

21:15.191 --> 21:20.528
"You like faking it, fine. You're stellar.
I'm the failure. l suck at faking it."

21:20.863 --> 21:23.698
-lt was not my finest hour.
-So where do things stand now?

21:23.866 --> 21:26.284
We're prepared
to offer half of everything...

21:26.452 --> 21:29.496
...and my client's retirement accounts.

21:30.665 --> 21:32.874
Take it all then. Everything.

21:33.042 --> 21:35.377
He still said no.

21:35.878 --> 21:38.672
-He hates me now.
-He doesn't hate you.

21:38.839 --> 21:41.216
His heart is broken.

21:44.387 --> 21:45.887
I think he hates you.

21:46.055 --> 21:48.014
I'm never letting you
out of the basement.

21:48.182 --> 21:51.434
Why don't we talk next week
and we'll see where things stand?

21:51.602 --> 21:53.186
-Okay.
-These things have a way...

21:53.354 --> 21:54.980
...of working themselves out.

22:10.079 --> 22:11.830
So why'd you become a vegetarian?

22:11.998 --> 22:14.249
I saw some cows slaughtered
one time.

22:14.417 --> 22:16.251
Barely touched your dinner.

22:16.419 --> 22:18.753
He's 28.

22:21.590 --> 22:24.676
This is hard for him, isn't it?
And you?

22:24.844 --> 22:27.178
The meditations help.

22:28.472 --> 22:29.764
Liz.

22:30.141 --> 22:33.226
You remember a couple of years ago,
when you threw yourself into...

22:33.394 --> 22:36.062
...the renovation of your kitchen?
You were consumed...

22:36.230 --> 22:38.148
...with being the perfect wife and cook.

22:38.315 --> 22:39.733
I was trying to make it work.

22:39.900 --> 22:42.777
Well, l think chanting and meditation
is the same thing...

22:42.945 --> 22:44.612
...in a different costume.

22:48.242 --> 22:49.951
Definitely give me that documentary.

22:50.119 --> 22:52.078
I've been thinking
about vegetarianism.

22:52.246 --> 22:54.205
My triglycerides
are through the roof.

22:54.373 --> 22:55.707
Yeah. Thanks for everything.

22:55.875 --> 22:57.917
Great to meet you.

23:02.298 --> 23:06.176
-What?
-Nothing. lt's just...

23:06.343 --> 23:08.303
...you know,
you used to look like Stephen.

23:08.471 --> 23:10.805
Now you kind of look like David.

23:10.973 --> 23:12.599
You know?

23:13.392 --> 23:18.146
What l meant was, you know how
people start resembling their dogs?

23:20.649 --> 23:23.109
Why would he say that,
we look like the same dog?

23:23.277 --> 23:24.819
-He was joking.
-Not funny.

23:24.987 --> 23:27.530
Well, he had five Heinekens.
He was bombed.

23:27.698 --> 23:29.908
Well, not funny.

23:30.076 --> 23:32.535
We don't look like the same dog.

23:33.329 --> 23:38.792
If anything, you're a collie
and l'm a Tibetan mastiff.

23:48.928 --> 23:51.971
Don't you wanna give me a chance
to miss you?

24:13.202 --> 24:15.829
It begins when
the object of your affection...

24:15.996 --> 24:19.541
...bestows upon you
a heady hallucinogenic dose...

24:19.708 --> 24:22.710
...of something you've never
even dared to admit you wanted...

24:22.878 --> 24:26.798
...an emotional speedball
of thunderous love and excitement.

24:26.966 --> 24:30.260
Soon you start craving that attention
with the hungry obsession...

24:30.427 --> 24:32.053
...of any junkie.

24:32.221 --> 24:35.723
When it's withheld, you turn sick,
crazy, not to mention resentful...

24:35.891 --> 24:39.060
...of the dealer who encouraged
this addiction in the first place...

24:39.228 --> 24:41.604
...but now refuses to pony up
the good stuff.

24:41.772 --> 24:44.732
Just frustrated, l'm concerned.
I don't understand.

24:44.900 --> 24:46.401
What don't you get?

24:46.569 --> 24:48.653
What's going on?
You don't look me in the eye.

24:48.821 --> 24:51.197
-You don't finish your--
-Nobody's asking you to make the bed!

24:51.365 --> 24:54.117
-You don't have sex with me!
-Sometimes I'm not in the mood!

24:54.285 --> 24:56.911
Goddamn him, and he used to
give it to you for free.

24:57.079 --> 25:00.081
Next stage finds you skinny,
shaking in a corner...

25:00.249 --> 25:02.250
...certain only that
you'd sell your soul...

25:02.418 --> 25:04.502
...just to have that one thing
one more time.

25:04.670 --> 25:07.297
Well, then why don't we discuss it?
Why don't we sort it?

25:07.464 --> 25:10.800
-Why don't we act like adults?
-Okay. Can I have a little space?

25:10.968 --> 25:12.594
-How about that?
-Meanwhile...

25:12.761 --> 25:16.180
...the object of your adoration
is now repulsed by you.

25:16.348 --> 25:19.225
-You don't always make me miserable.
-There's a comfort.

25:19.393 --> 25:22.854
I just-- Sometimes l need to
come home...

25:23.522 --> 25:25.273
...and have a little David time.

25:25.441 --> 25:28.776
He looks at you like someone
he's never met before.

25:28.944 --> 25:30.695
-ls that okay?
-Yeah. No, it's fine.

25:30.863 --> 25:33.948
And not have to, like, you know,
justify it.

25:34.116 --> 25:37.243
The irony is
you can hardly blame him.

25:37.411 --> 25:40.788
I mean, check yourself out.
You're a mess.

25:40.956 --> 25:43.458
Unrecognizable
even to your own eyes.

25:43.626 --> 25:45.627
You asked me to come here?
Here l am.

25:45.794 --> 25:47.629
And it turned into something else.

25:47.796 --> 25:50.256
-Didn't it?
-You are such a child.

25:54.428 --> 25:57.805
-Right. I can't take this anymore.
-Great. Perfect.

25:57.973 --> 26:01.309
That's a great response
to a conversation.

26:01.477 --> 26:02.518
Goddamn it.

26:02.686 --> 26:07.607
You have now reached
infatuation's final destination.

26:08.484 --> 26:14.447
The complete
and merciless devaluation of self.

26:48.649 --> 26:50.024
You wanna go away for a year?

26:50.192 --> 26:52.318
Do you know what I felt
when l woke up, Delia?

26:52.486 --> 26:57.073
Nothing. No passion, no spark,
no faith, no heat. Absolutely nothing.

26:57.241 --> 27:00.451
I've gotten past the point where
I can be calling this a bad moment.

27:00.619 --> 27:03.955
And it just terrifies me. Jesus,
this is like worse than death to me...

27:04.123 --> 27:06.958
...the idea that this is the person
I'm gonna be from now on.

27:07.126 --> 27:08.418
This happens to people.

27:08.585 --> 27:10.670
They fall in love in their 20s,
get married...

27:10.838 --> 27:13.798
...do the granite countertop,
white-picket fence in their 30s...

27:13.966 --> 27:16.342
...and somewhere they realize,
"This is not for me."

27:16.510 --> 27:20.013
So they fail and they fall down,
they hurt like hell, they straighten up...

27:20.180 --> 27:22.432
...and march their asses
to the shrink's office.

27:22.599 --> 27:26.102
-They can't just check out.
-l am not checking out.

27:26.270 --> 27:27.770
I need to change.

27:27.938 --> 27:30.189
You have a support system
here, Liz.

27:30.357 --> 27:32.191
You have friends and family
who love you.

27:32.359 --> 27:36.029
And do you feel my love for you?
My support for you? No.

27:36.196 --> 27:38.698
There's, like, nothing. l have no pulse.

27:41.243 --> 27:43.661
-l am going to Italy.
-ltaly. Why ltaly?

27:43.829 --> 27:46.289
-What did you have for lunch?
-l don't know. A salad.

27:46.457 --> 27:51.669
Exactly. l used to have this appetite
for food, for my life...

27:51.837 --> 27:52.962
...and it is just gone.

27:54.548 --> 27:58.843
I wanna go someplace
where l can marvel at something.

27:59.011 --> 28:02.430
Language, gelato,
spaghetti, something.

28:02.598 --> 28:05.516
-You're talking like a college kid.
-l've been acting like one.

28:05.684 --> 28:09.228
Since I was 1 5, I've either been
with a guy or breaking up with a guy.

28:09.396 --> 28:12.356
I have not given myself
two weeks of a breather...

28:12.524 --> 28:15.818
...to just deal with, you know, myself.

28:18.155 --> 28:20.031
What's going on
with you and David?

28:28.665 --> 28:29.749
What, did you fall out?

28:30.084 --> 28:32.126
I don't know how to be here.

28:32.294 --> 28:35.922
You wanna know how to be here?
Stop constantly waiting for something.

28:40.594 --> 28:45.306
I'm going to Italy and then l'm going
to David's guru's ashram in lndia...

28:45.474 --> 28:48.893
...and l'm going to end the year
in Bali.

28:52.064 --> 28:53.439
That's what l'm gonna do.

28:53.607 --> 28:56.275
That's harder to argue with.
The beaches are nice. But why?

28:56.443 --> 28:58.444
-Ketut told me I would.
-Guy with no teeth.

28:58.612 --> 28:59.695
When you're desperate...

28:59.863 --> 29:02.365
...and some guy who,
yes, looks a little like Yoda...

29:02.533 --> 29:05.785
...hands you a prophecy,
you have to respond.

29:05.953 --> 29:08.121
-Do you need a Xanax?
-Always.

29:09.123 --> 29:12.458
Okay, l'm just gonna say it.
I'm gonna say it and be done with it.

29:12.626 --> 29:13.709
What if it doesn't work?

29:18.215 --> 29:21.050
My whole life
fits in a 1 2-foot-square box.

29:22.803 --> 29:25.471
You know how many times
I hear that in a day?

29:25.639 --> 29:27.932
Most of them never come back
for their whole life.

29:32.813 --> 29:33.980
-Hello?
-Liz.

29:34.148 --> 29:37.108
Good news. Stephen just signed
the divorce papers.

29:45.826 --> 29:50.037
I'll probably be back in a week,
penniless with dysentery.

29:50.205 --> 29:52.081
You're my hero.

30:05.804 --> 30:07.180
Hey.

30:08.765 --> 30:11.309
If you stay,
we'll go out for lndian every night.

30:13.395 --> 30:15.271
You never asked me to stay.

30:21.570 --> 30:23.446
Go, go, go.

30:43.550 --> 30:45.176
You know what's funny?

30:45.344 --> 30:48.971
This is the first time in my life
there's no one waiting at home for me.

30:49.139 --> 30:51.015
I don't even have a home
to come back to.

30:51.183 --> 30:52.516
Oh, God. You'll make friends.

30:52.684 --> 30:54.810
You'll make friends with a backpack,
of course.

30:54.978 --> 30:56.437
It'd be great to get away.

30:56.605 --> 31:00.775
Andy and l were talking about getting
a little villa in Florence for a month.

31:00.943 --> 31:03.611
You know, and in 1 0 years,
when Jack is older....

31:04.613 --> 31:05.947
What?

31:08.033 --> 31:10.952
You know why l was giving you
such a hard time?

31:12.204 --> 31:15.706
I love my job, my guy and my kid,
but....

31:17.626 --> 31:19.627
I wish I could go.

31:28.804 --> 31:30.304
I love you and l'm proud of you.

31:31.306 --> 31:32.848
Now go.

31:56.456 --> 31:58.332
There is a wonderful
old Italian joke...

31:58.500 --> 32:00.835
...about a poor man
who goes to church every day...

32:01.003 --> 32:05.339
...and prays before the statue
of a great saint, begging:

32:06.133 --> 32:12.138
"Dear saint, please, please, please
let me win the lottery."

32:12.973 --> 32:15.766
Finally, the exasperated statue
comes to life...

32:15.934 --> 32:18.144
...and looks down at the begging man
and says:

32:18.353 --> 32:23.733
"My son, please, please, please
buy a ticket."

32:24.568 --> 32:26.360
So now l get the joke.

32:26.528 --> 32:29.155
And l've got three tickets.

32:49.634 --> 32:52.678
You heat the water on the stove.

32:54.598 --> 32:56.891
So if I want to bathe...?

32:57.059 --> 33:02.063
You put the water in the tub.

33:04.483 --> 33:06.400
Okay.

33:06.735 --> 33:13.157
Yeah. lt doesn't really seem like
enough water to bathe in.

33:15.243 --> 33:17.745
Not enough.

33:17.913 --> 33:19.663
Yes, it's enough.

33:19.831 --> 33:23.209
Fill it up three, four, five times.

33:23.710 --> 33:26.921
Everything that's important
gets cleaned.

33:43.146 --> 33:45.606
Is this safe? This...

33:46.858 --> 33:49.110
...scaffolding? Scaffol--

33:49.277 --> 33:51.278
It holds up the ceiling.

33:51.446 --> 33:54.657
Otherwise it will fall apart.

33:55.325 --> 33:56.951
Everything falls apart, my dear.

33:57.119 --> 34:01.789
The only thing permanent in life
is family.

34:05.877 --> 34:07.086
You're not married.

34:08.255 --> 34:10.214
No, divorziata.

34:10.632 --> 34:12.257
Why divorced?

34:16.179 --> 34:17.596
We broke it.

34:20.641 --> 34:23.143
You're more happy now?

34:27.524 --> 34:29.108
I have one rule.

34:29.650 --> 34:34.822
No strange men spending the night.

34:34.989 --> 34:37.699
You American girls
when you come to ltaly...

34:37.868 --> 34:40.202
...all you want is pasta...

34:40.370 --> 34:42.413
...and sausage.

34:47.252 --> 34:48.335
I'll take it.

34:48.670 --> 34:49.962
Good. You chose well.

35:24.164 --> 35:25.206
Cappuccino.

35:25.373 --> 35:28.542
-lt's a zoo in here.
-And my ltalian sucks.

35:28.710 --> 35:31.212
-How long have you been here?
-Two weeks. You?

35:31.379 --> 35:33.297
Six weeks. You'll get better.

35:33.965 --> 35:35.216
Two cappuccinos, please.

35:35.383 --> 35:37.092
And warm the milk this time.

35:37.260 --> 35:39.303
Yesterday it was too hot
and burned my tongue.

35:39.930 --> 35:41.764
-You like Napoleons?
-Of course.

35:41.932 --> 35:44.308
And two Napoleons, please.

35:45.060 --> 35:47.144
Your Italian is fantastic.

35:47.312 --> 35:50.689
I have a wonderful tutor.
I'll give you his number if you like.

35:50.857 --> 35:53.442
-He's really good and he needs work.
-Oh, great.

35:53.610 --> 35:55.527
Are you Dutch? German?

35:55.695 --> 35:59.323
Swedish. Even colder people,
if you can imagine.

35:59.991 --> 36:02.868
-l'm Liz, by the way.
-Sofi.

37:28.621 --> 37:29.663
You can say:

37:34.794 --> 37:35.919
It's past.

37:47.682 --> 37:49.016
Too fast, but okay.

37:49.184 --> 37:50.309
You can say:

37:53.146 --> 37:54.521
Yeah.

38:02.781 --> 38:04.198
What a beautiful word.

38:04.366 --> 38:07.701
Come on, it's "let's cross over."
It's so ordinary.

38:08.536 --> 38:12.873
No, it's the perfect combination
of ltalian sounds.

38:13.041 --> 38:17.211
It's the wistful "ah," the rolling trill,
the soothing "ess."

38:17.545 --> 38:19.380
-That's true.
-l love it.

38:19.756 --> 38:22.091
All right, let me teach you a word.

38:26.679 --> 38:32.017
Therapist.

38:32.185 --> 38:33.977
-Come on.
-Good. You gotta learn humor.

38:34.145 --> 38:35.646
-lt's not.
-Come on. Cheers.

38:44.072 --> 38:46.240
-Shall we continue Tuesday at 5?
-Yes.

38:46.408 --> 38:49.576
-With another bottle of the therapy?
-Of course.

38:49.744 --> 38:52.121
-You're doing very well, Liz.
-Thank you.

38:52.288 --> 38:54.456
And you must be very polite
with yourself...

38:54.624 --> 38:56.125
...when you learn something new.

38:56.292 --> 38:58.085
Yes. Grazie, I agree.

38:58.253 --> 39:01.797
But your English-- How are you
even talking to me like this right now?

39:01.965 --> 39:04.508
I think you're gonna teach me
more than I teach you.

39:04.676 --> 39:06.593
You have good Italian. Very good.

39:06.928 --> 39:08.220
All right.

39:52.307 --> 39:54.808
I am alone.

41:53.761 --> 41:56.263
I feel so guilty.
I've been in Rome for three weeks...

41:56.431 --> 41:58.932
...all l've done is learn
a few ltalian words and eat.

41:59.100 --> 42:00.934
You feel guilty
because you're American.

42:01.102 --> 42:02.978
You don't know
how to enjoy yourself.

42:03.146 --> 42:05.355
-l beg your pardon?
-lt's true.

42:05.523 --> 42:08.775
Americans know entertainment,
but don't know pleasure.

42:09.444 --> 42:12.195
This is Luca Spaghetti, by the way,
you know.

42:12.780 --> 42:14.906
Your name is Luca Spaghetti?

42:15.074 --> 42:16.950
Yes, that's what our family is called.

42:17.118 --> 42:19.953
We invented it.
I'm serious. Listen to me.

42:20.121 --> 42:22.497
You want to know your problem?
Americans.

42:22.832 --> 42:25.083
You work too hard.
You get burned out.

42:25.251 --> 42:27.919
Then you come home
and spend the whole weekend...

42:28.087 --> 42:30.714
...in your pajamas in front of the TV.

42:30.882 --> 42:32.633
That's not far off, actually.

42:32.800 --> 42:36.970
But you don't know pleasure.
You have to be told you've earned it.

42:37.138 --> 42:40.057
You see a commercial that says,
"It's Miller time"...

42:40.224 --> 42:44.311
...and you say, "That's right.
Now I will go to buy a six-pack."

42:44.479 --> 42:49.316
And drink the whole thing and wake up
the next morning and you feel terrible.

42:49.484 --> 42:52.319
But an ltalian doesn't need
to be told.

42:52.487 --> 42:56.698
He walks by a sign that says,
"you deserve a break today"...

42:56.866 --> 42:58.325
...and he says, "Yeah, l know.

42:58.493 --> 43:02.329
That's why I'm planning on
taking a break at noon...

43:02.497 --> 43:05.749
...to go over to your house
and sleep with your wife."

43:07.335 --> 43:09.836
We call it "dolce far niente."

43:10.004 --> 43:11.421
It means...

43:11.756 --> 43:15.509
...the sweetness of doing nothing.
We are masters of it.

43:28.314 --> 43:30.232
He's right. He says...

43:30.400 --> 43:32.150
...you can't learn ltalian like this.

43:32.318 --> 43:36.738
You don't speak the language just with
your mouth, speak it with your hands.

43:36.906 --> 43:37.948
Like this?

43:41.536 --> 43:44.204
Okay. ls yelling.

43:48.209 --> 43:49.459
'THAT MEAL WAS EXCELLENT'

43:59.679 --> 44:01.054
'SUCK IT'

44:03.224 --> 44:05.016
All this gives me a stomachache.

44:06.185 --> 44:07.436
'SCREW YOU'

44:08.312 --> 44:11.231
-l think that's my neighbor Lorenzo.
-Charming.

44:14.736 --> 44:17.195
ANOTHER WAY
TO SAY 'SCREW YOU'

44:28.124 --> 44:30.542
So anyway, to start off l'd say....

44:30.710 --> 44:32.377
Excuse me.

44:32.920 --> 44:33.962
Come here.

44:36.632 --> 44:37.674
For the table...

44:37.842 --> 44:40.927
...a big platter
of artichoke alla giudia...

44:41.262 --> 44:42.596
...prosciutto with melon...

44:42.764 --> 44:45.140
...and eggplant
with ricotta affumicata.

44:46.058 --> 44:48.018
Then spaghetti alla carbonara...

44:48.686 --> 44:50.771
...pappardelle with ragu of rabbit...

44:50.938 --> 44:52.898
...and linguini with clams.

44:53.065 --> 44:55.275
Then tripe alla romana...

44:55.443 --> 44:56.443
...and saltimbocca.

44:56.611 --> 44:59.613
And two more liters
of the vino sfuso from Genzano.

44:59.781 --> 45:01.072
Thank you.

45:03.493 --> 45:06.286
You did it. Yes.

45:06.454 --> 45:08.455
Liz Gilbert,
you are a Roman woman now.

45:08.623 --> 45:10.916
No, only honorary.

45:11.083 --> 45:13.043
That is a real Roman woman.

45:16.589 --> 45:19.424
Yeah, with a lot
of international friends.

45:19.592 --> 45:21.134
That one, I'd bite.

45:22.637 --> 45:24.846
Maybe you and Rome
just have different words.

45:25.014 --> 45:26.640
-Different words?
-Yeah.

45:26.808 --> 45:30.477
Yeah. lt's like each city has a word,
if you really think about it.

45:30.645 --> 45:33.480
Like, what is the word for London?

45:33.648 --> 45:36.107
-l would say "stuffy."
-l would agree with that.

45:36.484 --> 45:39.653
-What's the word for Stockholm?
-Are you kidding? "Conform."

45:39.821 --> 45:41.112
And New York?

45:41.280 --> 45:44.658
"Ambition" or "soot."

45:44.992 --> 45:47.160
What's the word for Rome?

45:47.578 --> 45:49.412
It's kind of difficult to think about.

45:49.580 --> 45:50.789
It's classic.

45:50.957 --> 45:52.457
"Sex."

45:55.044 --> 45:56.670
Of course.

46:23.030 --> 46:26.700
So, what's your word, Liz?
I'm curious. l can't figure it out.

46:26.868 --> 46:28.535
Well....

46:31.247 --> 46:33.373
It might be....

46:34.166 --> 46:39.045
It started as "daughter."
I was good at that. And then...

46:39.505 --> 46:42.382
..."wife." Not so good.

46:42.550 --> 46:44.384
"Girlfriend."

46:45.386 --> 46:47.053
Not so good.

46:47.221 --> 46:48.680
My word's "writer."

46:48.848 --> 46:52.350
Yeah, but that's what you do.
That isn't who you are, no?

46:52.852 --> 46:55.020
Maybe you're a woman
in search of her word.

47:08.284 --> 47:12.579
Hey, Sofi, it's Liz. Let's go to Naples.
Maybe my word is "pizza."

47:27.094 --> 47:30.680
Listen, lady, I am only 7, but l
can tell you're a complete moron...

47:30.848 --> 47:33.183
...because I am from Naples.

47:33.768 --> 47:36.061
I love this place,
but Giovanni said to watch out.

47:36.228 --> 47:38.772
His cousin got mugged here
in a museum.

47:38.940 --> 47:41.441
-Are you serious?
-Watch out for the scooter. Yeah.

47:55.289 --> 47:58.959
I'm in love. l'm having
a relationship with my pizza.

47:59.335 --> 48:02.420
You look like you're breaking up
with the pizza. What's the matter?

48:02.588 --> 48:03.797
I can't.

48:03.965 --> 48:06.424
What do you mean, you can't?
This is pizza in Napoli.

48:06.592 --> 48:08.760
It is your moral imperative
to eat that pizza.

48:09.136 --> 48:13.264
I want to,
but I've gained, like, 1 0 pounds.

48:13.432 --> 48:15.433
I mean, l've got this....

48:15.601 --> 48:17.811
Right here. What's it called?
What's the word?

48:18.104 --> 48:20.313
A muffin top.

48:21.148 --> 48:22.816
I have one too.

48:22.984 --> 48:25.735
I unbuttoned my jeans
five minutes ago just looking at this.

48:25.903 --> 48:27.195
Let me ask you a question.

48:27.363 --> 48:30.448
In all the years you've ever
undressed in front of a gentleman....

48:30.950 --> 48:34.285
-Hasn't been that many.
-All right, well...

48:34.704 --> 48:36.329
...has he ever asked you to leave?

48:36.497 --> 48:39.290
-Has he ever walked out? Left?
-No.

48:39.667 --> 48:41.126
Because he doesn't care.

48:41.293 --> 48:44.004
He's in a room with a naked girl.
He's won the lottery.

48:44.171 --> 48:48.008
I'm so tired of saying no
and then waking up in the morning...

48:48.175 --> 48:51.136
