at a very, very good price right now.

01:42:42.365 --> 01:42:44.282
Paradise.

01:42:47.036 --> 01:42:49.245
-l'll take it.
-People in Bali understand...

01:42:49.413 --> 01:42:52.457
...in order to stay happy,
must always know where you are...

01:42:52.667 --> 01:42:54.125
...every moment.

01:42:54.293 --> 01:42:58.922
Right here is perfect balance.
Right at meeting of heaven and earth.

01:43:00.132 --> 01:43:02.884
Not too much God,
not too much selfish.

01:43:03.052 --> 01:43:06.137
Otherwise, life too crazy.

01:43:06.305 --> 01:43:09.766
You lose balance, you lose power.

01:43:09.934 --> 01:43:13.311
In morning,
you do meditation from India.

01:43:13.813 --> 01:43:15.814
Serious. Very serious.

01:43:15.982 --> 01:43:18.108
In day, you enjoy Bali.

01:43:27.994 --> 01:43:30.996
Then in afternoon, come see me.

01:43:38.212 --> 01:43:40.964
End of day, you do new meditation.

01:43:41.132 --> 01:43:42.173
Very simple.

01:43:42.341 --> 01:43:46.011
Sit in silence and smile.

01:43:47.263 --> 01:43:48.638
I feel balanced already.

01:43:48.806 --> 01:43:50.181
Not so easy, Liss.

01:43:50.349 --> 01:43:55.020
Smile with face. Smile with mind.

01:43:55.229 --> 01:43:58.231
Even smile in liver.

01:44:00.151 --> 01:44:02.527
See you later, alligator.

01:45:15.434 --> 01:45:17.060
Oh, God.

01:45:17.228 --> 01:45:19.437
-Are you all right?
-Are you blind?

01:45:19.605 --> 01:45:24.442
-Please, let me take you to a doctor.
-l'm fine. l just--

01:45:28.114 --> 01:45:29.781
It looks bad.

01:45:29.949 --> 01:45:31.616
Very bad, Liss.

01:45:31.826 --> 01:45:34.953
-What happen?
-This idiot ran me off the road.

01:45:35.162 --> 01:45:36.955
A man? He rich?

01:45:38.290 --> 01:45:39.749
This very hot.

01:45:40.251 --> 01:45:43.294
-You need healer.
-l have you. You're a medicine man.

01:45:43.462 --> 01:45:47.090
-No. You need Wayan.
-Yeah.

01:45:57.017 --> 01:46:00.645
Jamu. Drink this.
Better than antibiotic.

01:46:06.986 --> 01:46:08.945
She make you drink this?

01:46:09.113 --> 01:46:11.156
-My name's Liz. What's yours?
-Tutti.

01:46:11.365 --> 01:46:13.491
Nice to meet you, Tutti.

01:46:13.659 --> 01:46:16.494
-Are you married?
-No.

01:46:22.501 --> 01:46:24.377
You sure? Not even once?

01:46:24.837 --> 01:46:26.754
Okay, well,
there was this one time...

01:46:26.922 --> 01:46:30.800
...but l find when l tell people in Bali
that I'm divorced, it upsets them.

01:46:30.968 --> 01:46:33.178
Me too, divorce.

01:46:33.387 --> 01:46:37.515
Divorce make you sad
and make you an outcast.

01:46:39.643 --> 01:46:42.520
You have no sex
for a long time, baby.

01:46:42.688 --> 01:46:44.189
I can tell by your knee.

01:46:44.398 --> 01:46:48.359
The cartilage very dry.
Hormones from sex lubricate joint.

01:46:48.527 --> 01:46:50.320
-Okay.
-l pray for you.

01:46:50.487 --> 01:46:53.114
We sisters.

01:46:53.574 --> 01:46:55.992
Armenia!

01:46:58.412 --> 01:47:00.038
Armenia from Brazil.

01:47:00.206 --> 01:47:01.998
Armenia, this is Liz from New York.

01:47:02.166 --> 01:47:04.375
-Hi.
-Lovely to meet you, Liz.

01:47:04.543 --> 01:47:06.294
Time for a banana root
hair treatment?

01:47:06.462 --> 01:47:09.547
-Yes, of course.
-lt makes the hair long and lustrous.

01:47:09.715 --> 01:47:13.885
Like Cher circa 1 975.

01:47:15.012 --> 01:47:16.679
Do you have a nice dress?

01:47:17.056 --> 01:47:18.056
One.

01:47:18.224 --> 01:47:20.225
Put it on tonight,
come to the Beach Shack.

01:47:20.434 --> 01:47:23.311
I'll introduce you to everyone.
The expats, the locals.

01:47:23.479 --> 01:47:25.396
You'll dance. You will love it.

01:47:25.564 --> 01:47:28.191
Oh, no, l don't think I can dance
with my leg like this.

01:47:28.359 --> 01:47:31.027
Of course you can. Leg no problem.

01:47:31.403 --> 01:47:33.196
You see.

01:47:33.822 --> 01:47:35.949
Now you have to come.

01:48:28.627 --> 01:48:32.255
Hi. Could I get a tequila on the rocks
with a lot of lime, please?

01:48:32.423 --> 01:48:34.132
Coming right up.

01:48:39.763 --> 01:48:41.264
Can l buy you a drink?

01:48:41.432 --> 01:48:42.974
No, thank you, I'm fine.

01:48:43.142 --> 01:48:45.143
I-- l almost killed you.

01:48:45.311 --> 01:48:48.313
I am sorry for that, really.

01:48:49.273 --> 01:48:51.649
-Hello.
-Hi.

01:48:51.817 --> 01:48:54.068
I'm sorry, really.

01:48:56.155 --> 01:48:57.655
Yeah.

01:49:08.375 --> 01:49:10.835
I'm sorry I'm laughing,
but it's amazing.

01:49:11.045 --> 01:49:14.672
I was actually listening to this song
in the car when the tape jumped.

01:49:14.840 --> 01:49:18.176
And l leaned over to fix it
and l ran you off the road.

01:49:18.927 --> 01:49:23.139
-Did you tell them to play it?
-No, no, no. I make them mixtapes.

01:49:23.349 --> 01:49:24.432
Mostly Brazilian music.

01:49:24.600 --> 01:49:28.853
But l'm also very much into
Phil Collins and Air Supply.

01:49:29.813 --> 01:49:33.191
You really shouldn't
say things like that out loud.

01:49:35.736 --> 01:49:36.778
Liz!

01:49:37.571 --> 01:49:41.157
-Hi.
-Oh, I see you've already met Felipe.

01:49:42.868 --> 01:49:47.205
Oh, of course. Two sad divorces.
You have so much in common.

01:49:50.793 --> 01:49:53.378
I have the perfect man for you.

01:49:53.962 --> 01:49:57.382
Just a little love affair.
Everyone has a little love affair in Bali.

01:50:00.010 --> 01:50:01.594
Isn't he charming? lan.

01:50:02.471 --> 01:50:03.721
Doesn't he look like Sting?

01:50:03.889 --> 01:50:06.391
Oh, yeah.
I made a very good mixtape of Sting.

01:50:12.898 --> 01:50:14.857
You should dance with him.

01:51:00.863 --> 01:51:02.405
Got you. Come on, l got you.

01:51:02.573 --> 01:51:04.949
That's gonna hurt tomorrow.

01:51:05.117 --> 01:51:07.618
All right. You know what?

01:51:07.786 --> 01:51:12.415
-That is it. We are going swimming.
-No, I don't even have my-- l--

01:51:12.583 --> 01:51:15.585
You don't have your-- You don't--

01:51:16.753 --> 01:51:17.962
You're so naked.

01:51:18.172 --> 01:51:20.965
Yeah, l'm naked.

01:51:21.300 --> 01:51:23.759
Armenia says everyone
should have a love affair.

01:51:23.927 --> 01:51:27.388
This is Bali. Everyone should have
a love affair in Bali.

01:51:27.556 --> 01:51:28.973
Yeah, but--

01:51:29.141 --> 01:51:31.142
Oh, God. No, no, no.

01:51:31.310 --> 01:51:33.686
-Love affairs are awesome, dude.
-They are. l just--

01:51:33.854 --> 01:51:35.480
I dated you 1 5 years ago.

01:51:35.689 --> 01:51:39.775
And l dated you six months ago.

01:51:39.943 --> 01:51:41.819
So l'm gonna go.

01:51:41.987 --> 01:51:43.988
You're not-- You're really--
You're going.

01:51:44.156 --> 01:51:45.990
But you're cute.

01:51:48.827 --> 01:51:50.328
I think I look good.

01:51:53.332 --> 01:51:54.373
Wait a minute.

01:51:54.541 --> 01:51:56.125
Oh, sorry. Here.

01:51:58.003 --> 01:51:59.670
-Thank you.
-Do you need a ride?

01:52:01.089 --> 01:52:03.007
That way I won't run you over again.

01:52:12.809 --> 01:52:14.936
Hello.

01:52:15.103 --> 01:52:17.939
-What time is it?
-Five a.m.

01:52:18.482 --> 01:52:21.025
Oh, you party hard.

01:52:21.193 --> 01:52:22.860
You really do.

01:52:23.028 --> 01:52:26.197
Thank you for....

01:52:26.365 --> 01:52:27.365
-The ride?
-Yeah.

01:52:27.533 --> 01:52:29.867
You're very welcome.
Need help with the bicycle?

01:52:30.035 --> 01:52:31.202
You keep it.

01:52:31.370 --> 01:52:33.371
Keep it? But it has a basket.

01:52:34.248 --> 01:52:36.249
It also has a bell.

01:52:56.144 --> 01:52:58.354
Good afternoon. How are you?

01:52:58.522 --> 01:52:59.564
What are you doing here?

01:52:59.773 --> 01:53:03.734
Well, l've brought you
Wayan's famous hangover cure...

01:53:03.902 --> 01:53:07.029
...because you drank
a little bit too much last night.

01:53:07.197 --> 01:53:11.242
And here it is.
Very delicious, as you can see...

01:53:11.410 --> 01:53:12.743
...and very tasty.

01:53:12.911 --> 01:53:15.413
Do you make it a habit of
walking into people's houses?

01:53:15.581 --> 01:53:18.541
Do you make it a habit of
sleeping with your front door open?

01:53:23.505 --> 01:53:25.047
It's a call. Moment.

01:53:26.592 --> 01:53:29.760
-Hello, darling. How are you?
-Can't get the coffee machine to work.

01:53:29.928 --> 01:53:32.263
Okay. l've told you 50 times.
It's very easy.

01:53:32.431 --> 01:53:34.432
You change the filter,
you add the coffee...

01:53:34.600 --> 01:53:37.727
...you add water and that's it.
How did you get into college?

01:53:37.894 --> 01:53:40.771
-How do l make it like you?
-Listen, l've been making coffee...

01:53:40.939 --> 01:53:44.942
...darling, for 40 years, so you have
to be patient with yourself. All right?

01:53:45.110 --> 01:53:48.613
Okay. So, what's up with you?

01:53:48.780 --> 01:53:52.074
-Nothing. l just can't talk right now.
-Holy shit. You're with a girl.

01:53:52.242 --> 01:53:54.118
-l have to go.
-Who is she? ls she hot?

01:53:54.286 --> 01:53:56.120
-Jesus, she's hot.
-Dad, if you hang up...

01:53:56.330 --> 01:53:58.581
...l'll call back and embarrass you.

01:53:58.749 --> 01:53:59.915
Dad, don't--

01:54:02.085 --> 01:54:04.462
That's a lot of "darlings," darling.

01:54:04.630 --> 01:54:06.130
Yeah. That darling was my son.

01:54:06.548 --> 01:54:09.634
I've called all my children "darling"
since they were little.

01:54:09.843 --> 01:54:12.803
Then there was a moment that
between the pets and the children...

01:54:12.971 --> 01:54:15.640
...l was confused,
so l called everybody "darling."

01:54:15.891 --> 01:54:17.391
Okay, you need to rest.

01:54:17.559 --> 01:54:20.061
Here is my number and my address.

01:54:20.228 --> 01:54:24.482
I'm gonna leave it here on the table,
in case you need a tour guide.

01:54:24.941 --> 01:54:26.651
A tour guide.

01:54:26.860 --> 01:54:31.072
And please, drink that up, because
it's gonna help you a big deal.

01:54:31.239 --> 01:54:33.366
Because you really look....

01:54:33.950 --> 01:54:37.495
-Ravishing?
-Astonishing.

01:54:37.663 --> 01:54:40.331
-Go away. Please.
-Okay. Drink it up.

01:54:40.499 --> 01:54:41.666
It's gonna be helpful.

01:54:49.257 --> 01:54:50.633
Hey, Mr. Tour Guide.

01:54:51.885 --> 01:54:53.344
Can we start with a coffee?

01:54:56.765 --> 01:54:58.182
Okay.

01:54:58.392 --> 01:54:59.850
What are these?

01:55:00.018 --> 01:55:01.852
These are rambutan.
They're delicious.

01:55:02.020 --> 01:55:05.606
It's like an orange made love
to a plum. Would you like some?

01:55:05.774 --> 01:55:08.526
When you put it that way,
yes, thank you.

01:55:09.194 --> 01:55:11.028
Excuse me.

01:55:12.406 --> 01:55:13.531
What is that?

01:55:14.616 --> 01:55:16.492
No, no, no.

01:55:16.660 --> 01:55:18.369
They taste like dirty feet.

01:55:18.537 --> 01:55:19.829
-Really?
-Dirty feet.

01:55:19.996 --> 01:55:21.539
They taste like feet.

01:55:21.707 --> 01:55:24.875
Look out. Nice.
How many places have you visited?

01:55:25.043 --> 01:55:29.213
I have 46 stamps on my passport.

01:55:29.423 --> 01:55:33.509
I happen to have 49 stamps
on my passport.

01:55:33.677 --> 01:55:35.720
-Forty-nine? I knew it.
-Yes.

01:55:35.929 --> 01:55:37.430
-Knew what?
-l knew it.

01:55:38.807 --> 01:55:41.183
We are both antevasins, my dear.

01:55:41.351 --> 01:55:42.393
What is that?

01:55:42.561 --> 01:55:44.729
Antevasin is....

01:55:45.564 --> 01:55:47.815
It's an in-between.

01:55:47.983 --> 01:55:50.067
It is the one who lives
by the border...

01:55:50.235 --> 01:55:53.654
...because they renounce
to the comfort of family life...

01:55:53.822 --> 01:55:56.824
...in order to seek "enlightment."

01:55:56.992 --> 01:55:58.909
I like your word.

01:55:59.077 --> 01:56:01.203
And l like the way
you say "enlightment."

01:56:01.371 --> 01:56:02.747
"Enlightment." I try.

01:56:02.956 --> 01:56:06.208
You're missing a syllable,
but I like it.

01:56:06.960 --> 01:56:08.586
It's beautiful, no?

01:56:08.754 --> 01:56:12.256
It's Pura Melanting,
which means "Temple of Prosperity."

01:56:13.049 --> 01:56:14.759
-Beautiful.
-Yup.

01:56:15.260 --> 01:56:17.928
-So next attraction of the tour?
-Yes.

01:56:18.096 --> 01:56:20.014
-Food from Bali.
-Oh, good. l'm starving.

01:56:20.182 --> 01:56:22.600
-Where should we go?
-To the best restaurant in town.

01:56:22.768 --> 01:56:25.102
-Of course.
-My place.

01:56:27.522 --> 01:56:28.898
Subtle.

01:56:29.775 --> 01:56:32.276
Did you always live in Brazil
before you came to Bali?

01:56:32.486 --> 01:56:33.778
No, no. Only for 20 years.

01:56:33.945 --> 01:56:38.199
Then l met my wife
and l moved with her to Australia.

01:56:38.366 --> 01:56:41.410
She traveled a lot
because of the job.

01:56:41.578 --> 01:56:45.122
-And I stayed home with the children.
-A good feminist husband.

01:56:45.290 --> 01:56:48.793
Yeah. Yeah. Didn't turn out to be
what she wanted, l'm afraid.

01:56:49.002 --> 01:56:50.461
-What happened?
-What happened?

01:56:50.629 --> 01:56:51.962
Well, the children were grown.

01:56:52.130 --> 01:56:57.802
And l run an import-export jewelry
business, so I could live anywhere.

01:56:58.011 --> 01:57:02.807
And Bali seemed like the perfect place
to recover from a divorce.

01:57:04.935 --> 01:57:07.937
And here l am. Here l am.

01:57:08.104 --> 01:57:09.772
-And you?
-Well, far less tragic.

01:57:09.940 --> 01:57:15.486
We were immature and really too
young to get married. We grew apart.

01:57:15.654 --> 01:57:17.154
Hearts were broken.

01:57:17.781 --> 01:57:19.657
Yes.

01:57:19.825 --> 01:57:21.909
Then it's the same.

01:57:27.541 --> 01:57:28.958
This is just perfect.

01:57:29.543 --> 01:57:31.418
So are you.

01:57:31.586 --> 01:57:34.463
You know what you are?
You're a falsa magra.

01:57:34.631 --> 01:57:36.507
-You know what that is?
-What?

01:57:36.675 --> 01:57:40.177
You are slender and elegant
in a distance...

01:57:40.345 --> 01:57:43.848
...but up close,
you are round and fleshy.

01:57:45.517 --> 01:57:47.560
Thank God for Brazilians.

01:57:51.481 --> 01:57:53.357
Stop that!

01:57:59.614 --> 01:58:01.699
You are a world traveler.

01:58:01.867 --> 01:58:03.200
He says that to everyone.

01:58:04.160 --> 01:58:05.494
Already make your money.

01:58:06.329 --> 01:58:09.331
You don't have young-man ambition.

01:58:10.166 --> 01:58:14.503
-He's good.
-You have three children.

01:58:14.671 --> 01:58:16.881
Two. That's a callous.

01:58:19.509 --> 01:58:20.843
And you have divorce.

01:58:22.095 --> 01:58:23.345
Very difficult.

01:58:23.513 --> 01:58:26.515
You loved her very much.

01:58:27.559 --> 01:58:29.101
You haven't healed that wound.

01:58:29.895 --> 01:58:34.106
Now you are scared
to open your heart.

01:58:35.066 --> 01:58:38.402
You are afraid
hurt will happen to you again.

01:58:39.112 --> 01:58:41.030
Only way to heal...

01:58:41.197 --> 01:58:43.741
...is to trust.

01:58:45.619 --> 01:58:49.872
This okay. To have broken heart
mean you have tried for something.

01:58:53.960 --> 01:58:57.087
Is it going to be broken again?

01:58:57.255 --> 01:58:59.423
He a good man, Liz.
You need a good man.

01:59:01.927 --> 01:59:03.594
Thank you.

01:59:03.762 --> 01:59:06.347
True. Ketut knows.

01:59:10.685 --> 01:59:13.562
I am so sick of people telling me
I need a man.

01:59:13.730 --> 01:59:17.775
You don't need a man, Liz.
You need a champion.

01:59:23.782 --> 01:59:27.117
-Some spring break, huh?
-Come on. You're moving like turtles.

01:59:27.285 --> 01:59:28.953
His enthusiasm is exhausting.

01:59:29.120 --> 01:59:31.455
